001package com.jwoglom.pumpx2.pump.messages.response.historyLog;
002
003import org.apache.commons.lang3.Validate;
004import com.jwoglom.pumpx2.pump.messages.annotations.HistoryLogProps;
005import com.jwoglom.pumpx2.pump.messages.helpers.Bytes;
006import com.jwoglom.pumpx2.pump.messages.response.currentStatus.AlarmStatusResponse;
007
008import java.math.BigInteger;
009
010@HistoryLogProps(
011    opCode = 5,
012    displayName = "Alarm Activated",
013    usedByTidepool = true
014)
015public class AlarmActivatedHistoryLog extends HistoryLog {
016    
017    private long alarmId;
018    
019    public AlarmActivatedHistoryLog() {}
020    public AlarmActivatedHistoryLog(long pumpTimeSec, long sequenceNum, long alarmId) {
021        super(pumpTimeSec, sequenceNum);
022        this.cargo = buildCargo(pumpTimeSec, sequenceNum, alarmId);
023        this.alarmId = alarmId;
024        
025    }
026
027    public AlarmActivatedHistoryLog(long alarmId) {
028        this(0, 0, alarmId);
029    }
030
031    public int typeId() {
032        return 5;
033    }
034
035    /**
036     * <table border="1">
037     * <caption>Parsed fields for AlarmActivatedHistoryLog:</caption>
038     * <tr><td><code>alarmId</code></td><td><code>Bytes.readUint32(raw, 10)</code></td></tr>
039     * </table>
040     */
041    public void parse(byte[] raw) {
042        Validate.isTrue(raw.length == 26);
043        this.cargo = raw;
044        parseBase(raw);
045        this.alarmId = Bytes.readUint32(raw, 10);
046        
047    }
048
049    public static byte[] buildCargo(long pumpTimeSec, long sequenceNum, long alarmId) {
050        return HistoryLog.fillCargo(Bytes.combine(
051            new byte[]{5, 0},
052            Bytes.toUint32(pumpTimeSec),
053            Bytes.toUint32(sequenceNum),
054            Bytes.toUint32(alarmId)));
055    }
056    public long getAlarmId() {
057        return alarmId;
058    }
059
060    /**
061     * @return the type of alarm
062     */
063    public AlarmStatusResponse.AlarmResponseType getAlarmResponseType() {
064        return AlarmStatusResponse.AlarmResponseType.fromSingularId(alarmId);
065    }
066}
